<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="220" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,366,1038]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,402,427]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A small species like the preceding, but with dark spots on dorsum, smooth veins and theca broadly sagittate (
<figureCitation box="[260,327,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,918,941]" captionTargetBox="[217,1363,209,878]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,195,894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 17. Male theca of Orthorapha s. s. (3 – 5), subgenus Balsania (6 – 7) and Lepyronoxia (8 – 17), lateral (A) and caudal aspect of tip (B): 3, O. cassidioides; 4, O. laeta; 5, O. invidia; 6, O. reducta; 7, O. sagittata; 8, O. obscurata; 9, O. inscripta; 10, O. decorata; 11, O. oculata; 12, O. bufo; 13, O. rana (type of O. glabrata); 14, O. subfasciata; 15, O. frontalis; 16, O. quadrimaculata; 17, O. sphaerata. Scale line: 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217116/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[312,327,439,463]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="220" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,366,1038]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,474,499]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Description.</emphasis>
Dark brown, paler on ventral half of face; marked with ivory as follows: W-shaped mark at tip of head forming slender median line ending in knob and divergent winglike lines from base extending onto sides of tylus, laterally overlaid by black muscle arcs (as in 
<figureCitation box="[737,820,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURE 34 – 36" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1630,1652]" captionTargetBox="[232,1357,202,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[217,1369,195,1606]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 34 – 36. Facial aspect (34), lateral aspect (35), tegmen in widest aspect (36) of Lepyronoxia. A, O. irregularis sp. nov.; B, O. frontalis (Stål); C, O. boliviana sp. nov.; D, O. obliqua (Jacobi), male; E, O. quadrimaculata (Lallemand); F, O. rana (Walker); G, O. decorata sp. nov.; H, O. oculata sp. nov.; J, O. sphaerata sp. nov.; K, O. subfasciata (A. &amp; S.); L, O. obscurata (A. &amp; S.), male; M, O. bufo (Walker). Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217121/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[789,820,547,571]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
B); crown with 
<number box="[997,1011,547,571]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="3.0">3</number>
spots, 
<number box="[1092,1106,547,571]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="1.0">1</number>
at base of tylus and a pair at base of crown near eyes; pronotum with 
<number box="[610,624,583,607]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="3.0">3</number>
pairs of irregular spots on either side of midline and a dash behind each eye, forming a chain; tegmina paler on veins at base of clavus, midlength and tips of corium. Head strongly produced, as long as pronotum in male, longer in female; frons strongly inflated in profile, angular at apex as in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Orthorapha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">O. boliviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; crown declivous, face horizontal, frons as low as clypellus at maximum expansion; head as wide as pronotum; lateral margins of pronotum much shorter than eye; tegmina rugulose, 
<number box="[1099,1134,727,751]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="1.7">1.7</number>
× as long as broad, veins strongly carinate throughout; hind wings as in 
<taxonomicName box="[676,796,763,787]" class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Orthorapha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliqua">
<emphasis box="[676,796,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">O. obliqua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[813,881,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1584,1606]" captionTargetBox="[276,1312,273,1556]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[265,1321,267,1560]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. New World Orthoraphini: habitus (A – B), hind wing (C – F) including detail of hamuli on costal margin (G – H), male abdomen in ventral aspect (J) and male genital capsule in lateral aspect (K). A, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) frontalis (Stål); B, F, H, O. cassidioides Westwood, female; C, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) obliqua (Jacobi); D, Orthorapha (Balsania) concinna (Stål); E, G, Orthorapha (Balsania) geminata (Jacobi); J, K, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) bufo (Walker)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217115/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[866,881,763,787]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Style abruptly narrowed preapically, tip small and hooked upwards. Theca shaft straight (
<figureCitation box="[644,713,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,918,941]" captionTargetBox="[217,1363,209,878]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,195,894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 17. Male theca of Orthorapha s. s. (3 – 5), subgenus Balsania (6 – 7) and Lepyronoxia (8 – 17), lateral (A) and caudal aspect of tip (B): 3, O. cassidioides; 4, O. laeta; 5, O. invidia; 6, O. reducta; 7, O. sagittata; 8, O. obscurata; 9, O. inscripta; 10, O. decorata; 11, O. oculata; 12, O. bufo; 13, O. rana (type of O. glabrata); 14, O. subfasciata; 15, O. frontalis; 16, O. quadrimaculata; 17, O. sphaerata. Scale line: 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217116/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[699,713,799,823]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
A), sagittate tip triangular, almost as wide as long, bearing slitshaped gonopore a quarter as long as shaft (
<figureCitation box="[641,708,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,918,941]" captionTargetBox="[217,1363,209,878]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,195,894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 17. Male theca of Orthorapha s. s. (3 – 5), subgenus Balsania (6 – 7) and Lepyronoxia (8 – 17), lateral (A) and caudal aspect of tip (B): 3, O. cassidioides; 4, O. laeta; 5, O. invidia; 6, O. reducta; 7, O. sagittata; 8, O. obscurata; 9, O. inscripta; 10, O. decorata; 11, O. oculata; 12, O. bufo; 13, O. rana (type of O. glabrata); 14, O. subfasciata; 15, O. frontalis; 16, O. quadrimaculata; 17, O. sphaerata. Scale line: 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217116/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
Fig. 
<number box="[693,708,835,859]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Length: male 
<number box="[905,940,835,859]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="3.9">3.9</number>
(
<typeStatus box="[955,1006,835,859]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">type</typeStatus>
) – 
<quantity box="[1035,1124,835,859]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
; female 
<quantity box="[1218,1356,834,859]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" metricValueMax="5.1" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="4.8" valueMax="5.1" valueMin="4.5">4.5–5.1 mm</quantity>
. Width across head or pronotum 
<quantity box="[434,572,870,895]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
